<subSubSection pageId="74" pageNumber="469" type="conservation">
<paragraph blockId="74.[1388,2595,729,1234]" pageId="74" pageNumber="469">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1390,1741,964,997]" pageId="74" pageNumber="469">Status and Conservation.</emphasis>
Classified as Endangered on The IUCN Red List. The Mount Cameroon Forest Shrew is known from only a single location (Mount Cameroon), with an extent of occurrence ofjust 483 km? and there is continuing decline in extent and quality of its forest habitat. It is threatened by habitat loss, presumably through conversion of land to agricultural uses and some logging operations. It might be common in its small distribution, but additional research is needed to confirm this.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
